---  

## 1. Project Structure  

```
imdb‑lite/
├─ src/
│   ├─ api/
│   │   ├─ auth/
│   │   │   ├─ auth.controller.ts          # JWT issuance & verification
│   │   │   ├─ auth.routes.ts              # Express routes for /login, /refresh, /logout
│   │   │   └─ jwt.strategy.ts             # Passport strategy (if used) – optional
│   │   ├─ movie/
│   │   │   ├─ movie.controller.ts
│   │   │   ├─ movie.routes.ts
│   │   │   └─ movie.service.ts
│   │   └─ health/
│   │       └─ health.routes.ts
│   ├─ core/
│   │   ├─ db/
│   │   │   └─ mongoose.ts                 # MongoDB connection singleton
│   │   ├─ logger/
│   │   │   └─ logger.service.ts
│   │   └─ security/
│   │       ├─ error.middleware.ts       # Central error handling
│   │       ├─ rate-limiter.middleware.ts
│   │       ├─ csrf.middleware.ts
│   │       └─ validate-input.middleware.ts
│   ├─ models/
│   │   ├─ user.model.ts
│   │   ├─ movie.model.ts
│   │   └─ review.model.ts
│   ├─ services/
│   │   ├─ auth.service.ts                 # Business logic for login / MFA
│   │   ├─ movie.service.ts
│   │   └─ audit.service.ts                # Tamper‑proof audit logging
│   ├─ middlewares/
│   │   ├─ auth-middleware.ts              # JWT & RBAC guard
│   │   └─ async-handler.ts                # Async route handler helper
│   ├─ configurations/
│   │   └─ app.config.ts                   # Loads env vars with zod validation
│   ├─ utils/
│   │   ├─ crypto.ts                       # Password hashing & token generation
│   │   └─ validator.ts                    # Schema validation helpers
│   └─ index.ts                            # Application bootstrap
├─ test/
│   ├─ unit/
│   │   └─ auth.service.test.ts
│   └─ integration/
│       └─ auth.routes.int.test.ts
├─ prisma/                                 # (optional) Prisma schema if used
├─ Dockerfile
├─ docker-compose.yml
├─ jest.config.js
├─ tsconfig.json
└─ package.json
```

*Why this layout?*  

- **CALM‑driven SOA** (ADR‑001) prefers *service‑oriented boundaries*; each domain (auth, movie, health) lives in its own folder, making the architecture **machine‑readable**.  
- **MongoDB + Mongoose** (ADR‑002) suggests keeping schemas (`models/*.ts`) separate from business logic (`services/*`).  
- **ADR‑003** dictates **JWT‑with‑inline‑RBAC**, so the authentication routes and middleware are isolated under `src/api/auth`.  
- **Testing isolation** (E4) uses a dedicated `test/` folder with unit and integration suites.  

---  

## 2. API Endpoint Specifications  

| Route | Method | Request Body (TypeScript interface) | Response (TypeScript interface) | Status | Description |
|-------|--------|------------------------------------|--------------------------------|--------|-------------|
| **/auth/login** | `POST` | `LoginRequest` | `LoginResponse` | `200` | Accepts `email` + `password`; validates credentials; returns **access JWT** (15 min) and **refresh token** (7 days). MFA optional. |
| **/auth/refresh** | `POST` | `RefreshRequest` (`{ refreshToken: string }`) | `RefreshResponse` | `200` | Rotates refresh token; issues new access JWT. |
| **/auth/logout** | `POST` | `{ refreshToken: string }` | `{ success: boolean }` | `204` | Revokes the supplied refresh token. |
| **/auth/mfa/verify** | `POST` | `MFAPayload` (`{ otp: string }`) | `MFAResponse` | `200` | Verifies one‑time code; marks session as fully authenticated. |
| **/movies** | `GET` | – | `MovieListResponse` | `200` | Returns paginated movie catalogue; requires **viewer** or higher role. |
| **/movies/:id** | `GET` | – | `MovieDetailResponse` | `200` | Retrieves a single movie; respects **RBAC** (admin can see deleted). |
| **/movies** | `POST` | `CreateMovieDTO` | `CreatedMovieResponse` | `201` | Creates a new movie; only **admin** allowed. |
| **/health/ready** | `GET` | – | `{ status: 'ok' }` | `200` | Liveness probe for Kubernetes. |
| **/health/live** | `GET` | – | `{ status: 'ok' }` | `200` | Readiness probe. |

```ts
// src/api/auth/auth.routes.ts
import { Router } from 'express';
import { login, refresh, logout, verifyMFA } from './auth.controller';
import { validate } from '../../core/security/validate-input.middleware';
import { LoginSchema, RefreshSchema, LogoutSchema, MFAVerifySchema } from './schemas';

const router = Router();

router.post('/login', validate(LoginSchema), login);
router.post('/refresh', validate(RefreshSchema), refresh);
router.post('/logout', validate(LogoutSchema), logout);
router.post('/mfa/verify', validate(MFAVerifySchema), verifyMFA);

export default router;
```

All endpoints are **behind` auth-middleware`** that enforces *deny‑by‑default RBAC* (ADR‑003).  

---  

## 3. Data Models  

### 3.1 User Model (`src/models/user.model.ts`)  

```ts
// src/models/user.model.ts
import { Schema, model, Document } from 'mongoose';
import bcrypt from 'bcryptjs';

export interface IUser extends Document {
  email: string;
  passwordHash: string;
  role: 'viewer' | 'reviewer' | 'admin';
  mfaEnabled: boolean;
  // audit fields (tamper‑proof)
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
}

const UserSchema = new Schema<IUser>({
  email: { type: String, required: true, unique: true, lowercase: true, trim: true },
  passwordHash: { type: String, required: true },
  role: { type: String, enum: ['viewer', 'reviewer', 'admin'], default: 'viewer' },
  mfaEnabled: { type: Boolean, default: false },
});

// Password hashing hook
UserSchema.pre('save', async function (next) {
  if (!this.isModified('passwordHash')) return next();
  const salt = await bcrypt.genSalt(12);
  this.passwordHash = await bcrypt.hash(this.passwordHash, salt);
  next();
});

// Method to compare password
UserSchema.methods.comparePassword = function (plain: string) {
  return bcrypt.compare(plain, this.passwordHash);
};

export const User = model<IUser>('User', UserSchema);
```

> **Rationale** – Aligns with **R3** (MFA, biometric) and **R6/R7** (identity hygiene). Storing a separate `role` claim fulfills **RBAC with deny‑by‑default** (E9).  

### 3.2 Movie Model (`src/models/movie.model.ts`)  

```ts
// src/models/movie.model.ts
import { Schema, Document, ArraySchema, Types } from 'mongoose';

export interface IActor extends Document {
  name: string;
  character?: string;
}

export interface IMovie extends Document {
  title: string;
  year: number;
  synopsis: string;
  actors: ArraySchema<IActor>;
  reviews: Types.ObjectId[]; // references Review collection
}

export const ActorSchema = new Schema<IActor>({
  name: { type: String, required: true },
  character: { type: String },
});

export const MovieSchema = new Schema<IMovie>({
  title: { type: String, required: true, index: true },
  year: { type: Number, required: true },
  synopsis: { type: String, maxlength: 2000 },
  actors: { type: ArraySchema, items: ActorSchema, default: [] },
  reviews: [{ type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Review' }],
});

export const Movie = model<IMovie>('Movie', MovieSchema);
```

- **Indexes** on `title` enable fast search (p95 latency target).  
- Embedding `actors` matches **R3** (flexible metadata) and optimises single‑document reads (E3).  

---  

## 4. Authentication Middleware Implementation  

### 4.1 JWT Utility (`src/utils/crypto.ts`)  

```ts
// src/utils/crypto.ts
import jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';
import crypto from 'crypto';
import { config } from '../configurations/app.config';

const ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL = config.jwtAccessTTL; // seconds (e.g., 900)
const REFRESH_TOKEN_TTL = config.jwtRefreshTTL; // seconds (e.g., 604800)

export function signAccessToken(payload: object, userId: string) {
  return jwt.sign(
    { sub: userId, ...payload },
    config.jwtSecret,
    { expiresIn: ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL }
  );
}

export function signRefreshToken(payload: object) {
  // JTI (JSE) for revocation tracking
  const jti = crypto.randomUUID();
  return jwt.sign({ ...payload, jti }, config.jwtRefreshSecret, {
    expiresIn: REFRESH_TOKEN_TTL,
  });
}

export function verifyAccessToken(token: string) {
  return jwt.verify(token, config.jwtSecret) as jwt.JwtPayload;
}
```

### 4.2 Auth Middleware (`src/middlewares/auth-middleware.ts`)  

```ts
// src/middlewares/auth-middleware.ts
import { Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';
import { verifyAccessToken } from '../utils/crypto';
import { Role } from '../models/user.model';
import { AuthGuardProps } from '../core/security/async-handler';
import { UnauthorizedError } from '../core/security/error.classes';

export async function authenticate(
  req: Request,
  _res: Response,
  next: NextFunction
) {
  const authHeader = req.headers.authorization;
  if (!authHeader?.startsWith('Bearer '))
    throw new UnauthorizedError('Missing token');

  const token = authHeader.split(' ')[1];
  try {
    const decoded = verifyAccessToken(token);
    (req as any).user = { id: decoded.sub, roles: decoded.roles };
    next();
  } catch (err) {
    throw new UnauthorizedError('Invalid or expired token');
  }
}

export async function authorize(allowedRoles: Role[]) {
  return async (req: Request, _res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
    const userRoles = (req as any).user?.roles ?? [];
    const hasPermission = allowedRoles.some(r => userRoles.includes(r));
    if (!hasPermission) throw new UnauthorizedError('Insufficient privileges');
    next();
  };
}
```

- **JWT validation** enforces **short‑lived tokens (≤ 15 min)** – directly addresses **THR‑001** (JWT spoofing) per **E6**.  
- **Roles** are embedded (`roles: 'viewer'|'reviewer'|'admin'`) – aligns with **E2**’s JWT‑inline‑RBAC.  

---  

## 5. Security Control Implementations  

### 5.1 Rate Limiting (`src/core/security/rate-limiter.middleware.ts`)  

```ts
// src/core/security/rate-limiter.middleware.ts
import rateLimit from 'express-rate-limit';
import { config } from '../../configurations/app.config';

export const apiLimiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: config.rateLimit.windowMs, // e.g., 60 * 1000 (1 minute)
  max: config.rateLimit.maxRequests, // e.g., 120 per minute per IP
  standardHeaders: true,
  legacyHeaders: false,
  message: 'Too many requests, please try again later.',
});
```

- **Why?** Mitigates **DoS** and brute‑force attempts (THR‑001/THR‑002).  

### 5.2 CSRF Protection (`src/core/security/csrf.middleware.ts`)  

```ts
// src/core/security/csrf.middleware.ts
import csurf from 'csurf';
import cookieParser from 'cookie-parser';
import { Request } from 'express';

export const csrfProtection = csurf({
  cookie: {
    httpOnly: true,
    sameSite: 'strict',
    secure: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production',
  },
});
export const parseCookie = cookieParser();
```

- Even though the service is primarily **stateless JWT**, cookies are used for **refresh‑token storage**; CSRF tokens prevent cross‑site misuse.  

### 5.3 Input Validation (`src/core/security/validate-input.middleware.ts`)  

```ts
// src/core/security/validate-input.middleware.ts
import { schema, ZodSchema } from 'zod';
import { Request } from 'express';

export function validate<T>(schema: ZodSchema<T>) {
  return async (req: Request, _res: Response, next: any) => {
    try {
      const parsed = schema.parse(req.body);
      (req as any).validated = parsed;
      next();
    } catch (e) {
      throw new BadRequestError(e.errors.map(err => err.message).join(', '));
    }
  };
}
```

- Guarantees **NoSQL injection prevention** (THR‑002) by enforcing strict JSON schemas.  

### 5.4 Token Rotation & Revocation (`src/core/security/token-revocation.service.ts`)  

```ts
// src/core/security/token-revocation.service.ts
import Redis from 'ioredis';
import { config } from '../../configurations/app.config';

const redis = new Redis(config.redis.url);

export async function isRevoked(jti: string, tokenType: 'access' | 'refresh'): Promise<boolean> {
  const key = `${tokenType}:revoked:${jti}`;
  const ttl = tokenType === 'access' ? config.jwtAccessTTL : config.jwtRefreshTTL;
  return await redis.exists(key);
}

export async function revokeToken(jti: string, tokenType: 'access' | 'refresh'): Promise<void> {
  const key = `${tokenType}:revoked:${jti}`;
  const ttl = tokenType === 'access' ? config.jwtAccessTTL : config.jwtRefreshTTL;
  await redis.set(key, '1', 'EX', ttl);
}
```

- **Why?** Implements **Refresh‑token rotation** (THR‑004) and meets **OWASP A07** requirements for preventing token replay.  

